\begin_layout Subsubsection*
After training,
 analyze the residual stream geometry.
 What structure is there?
 How does it relate to the belief geometries of the component processes?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection*
Setup
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
I construct a non-ergodic dataset from 8 Mess3 instances with distinct parameter pairs 
\begin_inset Formula $(\alpha,x)$
\end_inset

 and train a small GPT-2 style transformer (3 layers,
 
\begin_inset Formula $d_{\text{model}}=64$
\end_inset

,
 context window 16) via next-token prediction.
 See Appendix
\begin_inset space ~
\end_inset


\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "sec:training-details"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset

 for full training details.
 All residual stream visualizations in the main text use PCA,
 which is unsupervised and therefore a weaker ask:
 any structure visible in PCA must be among the dominant directions of variance,
 not a consequence of fitting to known labels.
 If this works,
 it means that it was computationally beneficial to encode the beliefs in 
\shape italic
prominent
\shape default
 dimensions of latent space (i.e.,
 high variance).
