\begin_layout Subsection*
Training dynamics
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
I track how the PCA geometry of the residual stream for a single instance (
\begin_inset Formula $\alpha=0.6,x=0.15$
\end_inset

) evolves over training steps across all layers (Figure
\begin_inset space ~
\end_inset


\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "fig:dynamics"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset

).
 The reason for this is to see whether the present structure requires learning,
 and if so,
 if it may only emerge late in learning when loss was already low.
 This is less important for the analysis where I used PCA to discover latents,
 but is a concern when using a supervised readout,
 since then the readout might overfit to the rich basis of the latent transformer dynamics even in absence of 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

true
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 structure.
 
