\begin_layout Subsection*
Limitations & further analysis
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Some of the simulation results seem compatible with the theoretical argument (simplex structure,
 state updates depend on evidence),
 but some clearly different (orthogonal spaces for different tasks).
 I would find it interesting to in a mechanistic interpretability style analysis find the cause of the discrepancies and see how the transformer actually implements Bayesian inference (if at all).
 To this end,
 I could imagine 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
trying to compute subspace angles for different instances,
 to get a sense of whether they are at least somewhat orthogonal
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
inspect the attention weights to see if they match what is outlined in the theory section
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
see whether the attention-weighted state indeed matches the 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

template
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 used for context inference
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
